        <title>My first game - BrainDef</title>
        <author>
            <name>Trost</name>
        </author>
        <link href="https://trost123.github.io/my-first-game-braindef.html"/>
        <id>https://trost123.github.io/my-first-game-braindef.html</id>
            <category term="gamedev"/>
            <category term="flash"/>

        <updated>2018-11-02T01:53:06+02:00</updated>
            <summary>
                <![CDATA[
                        <img src="https://trost123.github.io/media/posts/2/IneK2YV1.png" alt="BrainDef flash game" />
                    Back in 2012, after reading a lot of success stories on flashgamedev.ru I&hellip;
                ]]>
            </summary>
        <content type="html">
            <![CDATA[
                    <img src="https://trost123.github.io/media/posts/2/IneK2YV1.png" alt="BrainDef flash game" />
                <p>Back in 2012, after reading a lot of success stories on <a href="http://flashgamedev.ru/">flashgamedev.ru</a> I decided to try creating a game myself.</p>
<p>This was my first experience of programming. I used Adobe Flash (which uses ActionScript3 as a scripting language). I used <a href="http://gamedev.michaeljameswilliams.com/as3-avoider-game-tutorial-base/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">this amazing tutorial</a> to learn how to create a basic shooter game in Flash, and then just remixed it a little.</p>
<p>In this game you can find references to my favourite games of the time: Team Fortress 2, C&amp;C, Wormix.</p>
<p>You can <a href="https://www.kongregate.com/games/trost123/braindef" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" title="Play BrainDef on Kongregate">play BrainDef on Kongregate</a>.</p>
<p><img src="https://i.imgur.com/lgfecFT.png" alt="BrainDef screenshot" width="722" height="502"></p>
            ]]>
        </content>
