    <entry>
        <title>Animated Banners - a first hobby job</title>
        <author>
            <name>Trost</name>
        </author>
        <link href="https://trost123.github.io/animated-banners-a-first-hobby-job.html"/>
        <id>https://trost123.github.io/animated-banners-a-first-hobby-job.html</id>
            <category term="flash"/>
            <category term="animation"/>

        <updated>2018-11-02T02:16:17+02:00</updated>
            <summary>
                <![CDATA[
                        <img src="https://trost123.github.io/media/posts/3/maxresdefault1.jpg" alt="" />
                    Somwhere in 2011 (on my first year of university) I started earning some pocket&hellip;
                ]]>
            </summary>
        <content type="html">
            <![CDATA[
                    <img src="https://trost123.github.io/media/posts/3/maxresdefault1.jpg" alt="" />
                <p>Somwhere in 2011 (on my first year of university) I started earning some pocket money as a freelancer. It wasn't much, but it was fun. I always wanted to become an animator - and this job was basically about animating adverisement banners in Adobe Flash.</p>
<p>Here are some examples of those banners. For more you can <a href="https://www.fl.ru/users/billcosby/portfolio/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">look into my fl.ru profile</a>.</p>
<p><object id="viewattachswf_d38e6192e875efd80b6bb3cbd2330d4f" style="visibility: visible;" data="https://st.fl.ru/users/bi/billcosby/upload/f_4e8dec3962052.swf" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="188" height="257"><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="never" /><param name="wmode" value="" /></object> <object id="viewattachswf_dc25ad4f25238c4c3715ca19a2c9666f" style="visibility: visible;" data="https://st.fl.ru/users/bi/billcosby/upload/f_4ec03fdcad9eb.swf" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="468" height="90"><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="never" /><param name="wmode" value="" /></object></p>
<p>The more I used Adobe Flash, the more creative I started getting. I found out that you can also do interactive stuff in flash, so I dived into simple scripting and created this: a plate-clock that shows real time, with a silly secret that you could find if you drag a knife or a fork with your mouse!<object id="viewattachswf_ed69d4f773657ec284ec32a98414e3f8" style="visibility: visible;" data="https://st.fl.ru/users/bi/billcosby/upload/f_4e78f787902ea.swf" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="500" height="500"><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="never" /><param name="wmode" value="" /></object></p>
<p>Here are some screenshots for those, who can't use flash in their browser:</p>
<p><img src="https://i.imgur.com/UXurmVH.png"></p>
<p><img src="https://i.imgur.com/gofl8L8.png"> <img src="https://i.imgur.com/WfZIXiQ.png"> <img src="https://trost123.github.io/media/posts/3/d7jvduqi.bmp" alt="" width="150" height="195"></p>
<p><img src="https://i.imgur.com/HC9wrCV.png"></p>
<p>This was an incredible experience and helped me learn basics of animation and scripting, which I later used to <a href="#INTERNAL_LINK#/post/2">develop flash games</a>.</p>
            ]]>
        </content>
